I came in on Friday evening (9/25/20), and while I didn't catch his name, I was deeply impressed by the service I received from the gentleman up front. I I requested an iced americano and he told me he didn't have any (which I'm used to). Before I could say anything he offered to go in the back and make some. This sense of leadership completely wowed me--never has anyone in a coffee shop offered this when I've asked (and I wouldn't even expect it either). You have a star player working for you. Thank you for the excellent service!

Great place to study; not too loud, not awkwardly silent. The tea selection is fantastic, and the gunpowder green is my go to for long, late-night study sessions. I love the large windows that let in lots of natural light and allow for some stellar people-watching. I always try to get a booth, since the tables better fit my laptop, a notebook, and a textbook (and they're comfy!), but there are a couple of tables that are also large enough that are not booths. There are easy to access outlets and free wi-fi. The quiche is delicious, and I find myself taking a study break to grab a tasty mimosa more often than I'd like to admit. All in all, Goldy's Corner is an excellent spot for a quick bite or for a comfortable and casual study session or coffee date.
